ğŸ“¦ 3. Dataset and Preparation Process (Detailed) 

At the heart of this project lies a custom-built dataset composed of humorous Turkish short stories called fÄ±kra. This stage involved not only collecting the data, but also refining and validating it to ensure high quality and ethical compliance for model training. 

 

ğŸ” 3.1. Data Collection 

Approximately 2,000 Turkish jokes were collected manually from a wide range of sources. 

Data Sources Included: 

Online humor platforms 

Nasreddin Hoca joke archives 

Traditional Turkish joke anthologies 

Public forums, PDFs, and digital joke books 

All jokes were simplified and standardized in Turkish to ensure linguistic consistency. 

